text: Adinassa is a small genus of African sea snails in the family Nassariidae. The type species was originally named Adinopsis skoogi in 1923, though the genus name Adinopsis had already been used for a genus of beetles five years earlier. Nearly 100 years later, the genus was renamed Adinassa and two new species were described. ==Species== There are three species within the genus Adinassa: * Adinassa barcai * Adinassa parrulai * Adinassa skoogi ==References== *
title: Adinassa
